               <head>Qasa'id of 'Urfi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by ʿUrfī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002009961" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1293C-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled collection of the qaṣāʾid or eulogies of the poet, Sayyid Jamāl al-Dīn Muḥammad Ḥusayn ibn Zayn al-Dīn ʿAlī ibn Jamāl al-Dīn Shīrāzī, with the takhalluṣ ʿUrfī (d. 999/1591), patronised at the court of the Timurid (Mughal) Emperor Akbar I (d. 1114/1605).</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 83r): completed by Ghulām [Ḥasan] ibn Muḥammad Shafīʿ, resident from the qaṣbah Gujarāt of Shāh Dawlah, 25 Rabīʿ al-S̲ānī in RY 5 of Emperor Muḥammad Shāh (1136)/22 January 1724.</p>
                        <p>Following the colophon (ff. 83v-84v) are systematic notes on various qaṣāʾid.</p>
                        <p>Neat to rough scribal nastaʿlīq and taʿlīq on variegated tinted papers (cream, pale pink, pale orange, pale bluish green, pale grey).</p>
                        <p>Dense interlinear and marginal annotations and corrections by multiple hands.</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound.</p>
                        <p>Paper dust wrapper (BEIC legal publication, Regulation XX of 1817); partial watermark (Britannia/Minerva in crowned oval frame); torn, folded, creased, stains; labels.</p>
                        <p>Condition fragile.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658492.0x000001 viaf_50413291">ʿUrfī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_50413291">عرفی</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
